node.text:
When we focus on “business,” we’re really focusing on:
- Relationship to MONEY
- Relationship to POWER
- Relationship to SELF-WORTH
- Relationship to SELF-TRUST
- Relationship to EGO/IDENTITY
⠀
If our business is entirely of our own creation, what we “create out of nothing” is literally a reflection of our own subconscious.
⠀
If you take one core principle from this, let it be this:
⠀
Your Entire Business Is A Mirror Of Yourself.
⠀
Watch the video to hear the rest of the transmission⚡️

Just two years ago, other peoples clarity around who they are triggered me.
⠀
When I heard people talk about the exact fashion they liked, or house design styles that felt like them, or even the specific business practices they liked the most...
⠀
...the trigger that came up inside of me was a feeling of upset and self-judgement that I didn’t know that much about myself.
⠀
I’d also take on whatever that person was saying as if it were a sales pitch, and think “well, they seem pretty clear—maybe I’ll just do that.”
⠀
If you’ve ever felt like that, you’re not alone.
⠀
And there is SO much to learn about yourself through other people.
⠀
So instead of being influenced and swayed when someone is clear as fuck about who they are...
⠀
Become inspired by their clarity to go find what’s true for YOU.
⠀
When you’re clear, someone else’s truth doesn’t threaten your own.
⠀
Learn who you are through my new 10-day mini course: 
⠀
👉🏼SELF-AWARENESS IS YOUR SUPERPOWER🎉🙌🏾
⠀
Over the course of 10 Days…
⠀
You’ll receive 10 emails from me
⠀
With one PDF or Video attached at the bottom🥳
⠀
In each document, you’ll dive deep into one specific self-discovery pillar a day....
⠀
And complete a powerful self-reflection exercise to provide you clarity on who you are,  and tools to walk through the world with more confidence.
⠀
Link in my bio to join!

Whether you’re deciding what to price your offer, what to do next during your brand pivot, or which tech platform to use to manage your team…
⠀
Strategic decision making is a key key key skill to learn 🔑 if you want to run an authentically successful business.
⠀
I’ve made a lot of decisions over the years.
Some were the right ones for me.
Some were absolutely the wrong ones for me.
All of them have taught me lessons about what it really means to run a business.
⠀

As scary as it is to share this, it’s even more important to have this conversation.
⠀
50% of eligible voters didn’t vote in the last election, and I was one of them.
⠀
You may feel like you don’t have a voice,
Or that your vote doesn’t matter,
or that you don’t have a good enough political education to make an educated decision.
Or maybe you’ve been afforded a lot of privilege, and haven’t had as big of an emotional draw to invest time and energy into educating yourself.
⠀
I get it.
I was the same way.
⠀
Because of my privilege,
Lack of education and dinner table conversations,
And avoidant attachment style,
⠀
I’ve only recently begun my self-education on our government,  political leaders, specific social causes, and actions I can take to make a difference.
⠀
I knew what I valued in my heart,
I just didn’t understand how absolutely wretched and disrespectful some people were being treated,
which my white + socio-economic + cis-hetero + able bodied privilege could truly make a difference.
⠀
Thank you for allowing me to share.
⠀
Get registered to vote.
It matters.

Rushed into strategizing on the next plan to cling to some semblance of control,
Or resisted a big change you’ve truly needed for yourself, your life, and your brand…

This video is for you.

Story-time; I had a big breakthrough this past weekend that feels like a year-long cycle is coming into a more clear decision around my BOOK!
⠀
And it required me to deeply heal my unhealthy masculine I’d been so looped up in from years of running in the top circles of the online fitness and business spaces.
⠀
Healing the intensity of the entrepreneur,
Allowing the creator to come back online with space and freedom,
And leaning into the student within so I could fully embody the words I was writing as the author of this book
⠀
We’re all absolutely necessary to be able to feel confident, grounded, and clear in getting this book out to the world.
⠀
Let me know what you think in the comments.

node.text:
The Truth About Being Around Powerful, Amazing People🔥

So as you may have noticed, I’ve spent a lot of time building friendship and community over the last few months: having incredible parties, with incredible people, having abso-fucking-lutely incredible conversations.

We had an “awesome time, drinking awesome shooters, listening to awesome music, and just soaked up each others awesomeness.”

The side that you don’t see, is what happens after.

Being around my fiancé @johnromaniello , for example, is an EXPERIENCE.

Not just because he’s well-spoken, intelligent, and charismatic—which is a sight to see.

But because he holds himself to the ✨absolute✨ highest standards of integrity ☝🏽 when it comes to self-honesty, being in integrity with his word, creating safety for others, and dropping his ego to be a better friend or partner to his loved ones.

He’s gone through the ringer in this life, and the amount of inner work he’s done is titanic.

And sometimes: the mirror🪞 he holds up through his embodied consciousness shines a light 💡 on all the places I still have work to do inside of myself.

His integrated inner work reflects back my own shadows; the darker parts of my consciousness.

If you’re not ready to face the darkest parts of you (that you’ve shamed, judged, or rejected), you’ll resist resist resist.

Being in the presence of people who:
- value themselves
- love themselves
- know they are worthy
- have done the inner work

…shows you where you have not.

For me and many others, I’ve experienced that as shame.

Shame in seeing where I have yet to meet myself, and resistance to diving into that dark space.

But that’s why being around “powerful” (embodied, conscious) people is such a life-changing catalyst:

Because if you’re willing to do the hard thing and meet yourself in your own darkness, the freedom and liberation on the other side will help you remember your wholeness and magnificence.

If you’re in this process: I see you. I feel you. I love you.

To everyone who has ever triggered a part of me I didn’t want to look at: fucking thank you.

Healing is a team sport.
If you feel me, comment below ❤️

The “feminine” is entirely different language than the masculine.

The way of the masculine essence is how we typically think of business: structure, systems, outcomes, data, tracking, closing, hard work, hustle culture—you know the vibe.

And you’re just about DONE with feeling like you don’t know how to be more feminine in your business or day to day.

What’s needed is to expand your window of tolerance.

“The edge of your comfort zone is where growth is. Jumping far outside of your comfort zone is just traumatic.” - @johnromaniello

The feminine aspects of you are quite literally an entire HALF of who you are.

Integrating it’s power back in will be a major part of healing the world:

- playfulness
- emotional expression
- body honoring
- unconditional love

Intelligence.
The mind.
Processes.
Problem solving.

The everything.
The intangible.
The magic.
The mystery.
The magic of the present moment.
The power of maintaining a connection to your loving heart presence, even in the darkest of moments.

In surrendering to my allowing my body to lead rather than only my mind—I’ve felt and experienced so immensely.

Deep wisdom.
Deep love.
Deep capacity to feel.
To experience wholeness.

That is her.

To feel. To play. To indulge. To submit. To surrender.

The nuanced, ever evolving experience of being alive.

I haven’t meditated in months, and I feel the MOST connected to my spirituality than ever before.

I’ll admit: I don’t meditate daily or weekly—only sometimes.
I don’t carve out time daily for my spiritual practice.
And I don’t feel the need to list off the “spiritual” things I do,

Because my entire life is spiritual.

I am living a spiritual life—infusing the principles of yoga, meditation, and breathwork into my every waking moment.

Spirituality” is not a neatly packaged persona or identity.

For me, spirituality is:

✨ connecting to the full spectrum of LIFE and aliveness that’s available to me, even the “lower vibration” stuff. the entire spectrum of polarity.

✨  a devotion living in integrity with the values of compassion, integrity, kindness, authenticity, and love. and in doing so, watching magic unfold before my eyes every single day.

✨  broadening my perspective of the world through the lens of people who live entirely different than I do, and in doing so—unlearning binary ways of thinking and becoming more inclusive in my understanding of humanity

✨  being intentional about my personal development as a way of life, so I can experience the MOST FULL life I possibly can in healing, growth, and connection to my truest self, which I feel is most in line with the universal laws.

✨  connecting to the “ascension/spiritual/5D” shit just as much as the human/reality/3D shit, because they’re equally as “spiritual.” It’s all a part of it.

That’s pretty much it.

And I feel the most connected to my spiritual self I ever have.

My life is aligning in ways I never thought possible, and it’s all due to my devotion to living through the above principles.

Your reminder to release more “shoulds” and “supposed to’s” from your world today.

xo,
Amanda

Marketing your product and brand doesn’t just have to do with the words you write or say—it has to do with what you embody.

More often than not, I hear coaches and entrepreneurs struggling to know whether or not what they do is coming across clearly.

“Do I have the right I help statement?”
“Is my title clear enough?”
“I feel like it’s hard to describe what I do with words.”

Well…use something other than words.

This is where we can all begin to embody a bit more of the “influencer” content creator archetype—by sharing our own lives, ourselves, and what we do on a daily basis to embody our expertise.

Your embodiment is felt experience of the kind of teacher you are.

Your education is exuded through your ESSENCE.

Are you embodying what you teach in your life?

SHOW PEOPLE.

On a meta-level: my intention is to help people be themselves, experience their own authenticity, and build a business that works for them.

By showing you when I’m having a difficult day,
Or when I’m taking time off,
Or the ease in which I attract clients,
Or my process for making decisions
Or how I navigate growth edges in my business,

I’m embodying my educational words of advice.

If you feel that disconnect in your marketing-brand-engagement with your audience

SHOW, along with tell.

node.text:
On finding empowerment to heal❤️‍🩹

One of the reasons it can feel so difficult to heal and transform patterns is because it requires you to be *the primary* active participant in the process.

In my most recent cycle of healing this week, I caught myself resisting the reality that no one is going to do the work to heal my own shit for me—yet again.

I sometime observe my mind kick and scream on the way there;
clinging tightly to the victimhood identity.

I wanted to stomp my feet, cry, and be held/taken care of.

I do have powerful support systems in my life—my partner (who holds the most epic space for the bigness of my emotions), my therapist, and friends.

But nothing truly, truly shifts within me until I overcome my own mind and move into the actual healing work.

Here’s how to do that:

1. Get present. Bring attention to your thoughts and resistance, and name it. “I’m noticing myself become victimized and overwhelmed by this experience and want something external to make it better.” This kind of calling yourself out takes it out of the SHADOW and into the LIGHT—and can be the hardest hardest part.

2. Find the part of yourself that does want to shift and heal. Let that part become louder than the resistance.

3. Use one of your tools. For me, I needed to use both some soft breathwork and body attunement to regulate my nervous system, and compassionate self-forgiveness—where I forgave myself for buying into the misidentification of myself as anything other than a worthy human being. This process may take some time, too—as the mind can be very strong.

The moment I called myself out, was the moment I was able to find the empowerment within me to heal myself and become that primary, active participant.

This is the shift from disempowerment to personal power—which is the most powerful way to heal. 

Sometimes, it takes a Herculean effort to do the thing—rather than just talk about the thing.

Our minds resist, resist, resist.

Let this be your reminder today that there is more peace on the other side of doing the work.

node.text:
I’m entering a phase in my life with an overwhelming amount of lightness.

After having spent many months in some deep darkness and shadow-y healing spaces, my body is still processing and—what my therapist calls—“tolerating pleasure.”

in observing this season of lightness come together, I look back at all of the healing I’ve done in various areas of my life.

health. fitness. business. spirituality. relationship. sex. friendship.

They did not all happen at once. There were seasons—years—spent focused on one or two key areas.

Also: my personal experience of the last 7 years has been all fucking in in each of these areas.

Like: keep going until I feel complete without stopping kind of all in.

And now, seeing each of the pillars of life-work come together, I’m observing this…lightness.

Ease.

Seamlessness.

Effortlessness.

As I’ve spent so much time unlearning, healing, and de-conditioning myself from all that is not mine.

The work is never done, but I can confidently say I have observed many cycles complete themselves.

*I also want to recognize the privileges which I was afforded and the absence of barriers in my personal experience of life as a middle-class white woman.

If you ever compare your journey to someone else’s, remember:

it’s powerful to focus and double down on one or two pillars at a time.

Integration takes time, effort, and resources. Honor where you are, and what you have.

Healing is possible.

Keep going.

xo,

Amanda

This past weekend, my friend @deshoots 📸set up an ice bath for us before our evening of play and dancing in the jungles of Tulum.

He said, “you can’t ‘conquer’ an ice bath with force and willpower. The only way to experience an ice bath is through deep, feminine surrender.”

I decided to go first.

Our guide walked me through the prepatory breathwork,
giving my body an opportunity to turn off fight or flight,
and allowing my mind to prepare.

As I submerged myself into the bath full of freezing water and bags of ice,
he said, “the only thing to do is to acknowledge that the pain is there
 If you try to ignore the pain, it will only fight back harder.”

“Hello pain,” I said.
“I acknowledge your presence.
And I will not allow you to control my experience.”

He guided us to breathe in a way that we simply become breath.
The more you let go of identifying with your physical experience,
the more you become consciousness.
If I shivered, he said “tell your body to stop shivering.”

It stopped.

All of the sudden, I barely felt the cold permeating my body.
I felt my warm body, melting the ice.
The ice was around my body like rocks, but not within me.
I was warm.

In that moment, I remembered that the mind controls the body.
And the spirit is at the center of it all.

Two minutes in, I burst into laughter and hysteria—allowing the bliss to overtake my entire body.

I had fully surrendered.
Liberated from the restrictions of ego and identity.

Some of the laughter was due to the fact that I had this same hysteria-bliss experience only two weeks prior, during a journey on my birthday.

In a moment, my consciousness aligned with the natural order of the Universe;
and pure BLISS and HYSTERIA overwhelmed by entire body,
and I surrendered to it in front of 40 people.
Feeling. Feeling. Feeling. 
Experiencing.
The ULTIMATE state of being.

One occurred during psychedelic journey, one entirely sober.

These moments aren’t what we all live in on a daily basis,
but they are reminders of the epic power we all hold within,
to dissolve the boundaries of reality as we fucking know it.

node.text:
Fuck you. Thank you.
⠀
Recently I was getting g a massage by my man @rhys.master , and we were chatting about his business.
⠀
In conversation, he was talking about his ultimate desire, he felt he needed to wait to act on.
And I asked him,
“Why don’t you just do that thing now?”
“Ahhhh shit don’t ask me that lol.” 🤣
⠀
Oops 🤷🏽‍♀️
in all seriousness: I don’t point out things unless I can sense someone is open to hearing or receiving that kind of feedback, because it can be  doozy.
⠀
Confronting yourself means asking the questions, like:
⠀
“Why do I do what I do?”
“Does this story serve my highest growth, or my safety and security?”
⠀
The thing is:
⠀
Our narratives and stories are what hold together our current reality—the one we are living in on a  day to day basis.
⠀
Our bodies are efficiency MACHINES—and any process that can be automated so as to minimize energy expenditure, it will.
⠀
So, our minds hide the growth and expansion available to us.
⠀
And when you catch yourself lying to yourself, the mind starts  to scramble, horrified that you just caught it in a lie.
⠀
Because what has to happen next,
Is action.
Is change.
Is facing your fucking fears.
⠀
If you really decided, right now, that you were more than ready and good enough to do the thing you “ultimately” want to do?
⠀
Well, you’d have to actually do it.
⠀
xo,
Amanda

Raise your hand if you feel personally victimized 🙋🏽‍♀️

If you’ve ever experienced the emotional rollercoaster of launching and having the intense emotional reaction to it as a result…you are not alone.

I’ve seen it over and over again as a business coach.

Excitement and inspiration to create a new thing.
Putting all of your eggs in one basket.
Setting a number goal that you’d like to receive.

And then, when launch comes around,
Completely emotionally crashing when people don’t sign up on the first day,
Feeling incredibly attached to the outcome and unable to release that,
Overworking to make sure you hit the goal because you won’t feel okay without it.

If this has been your experience: I’m so sorry.

I hope this post can better prepare you, because launching a new product (or the launch process in general) can activate so many different trauma responses.

Fear of failure.
Fear of success.
Perfectionism.
People pleasing.
Worthiness.
Attachment wounding.
Self-judgement/loathing.

To learn how to go into your next launch to minimize that emotional rollercoaster, you can grab The Aligned Launch Masterclass — a 2 hour course designed to support you in creating sustainable, successful, and grounded launches.

Link in my bio <3

Your Friday Reminder that the work, works.
⠀
I used to have this feeling during my healing journey that I’ll just always be in the thick of it.
⠀
“Will I ever catch up to myself?” I’d ask.
⠀
It seemed like new awarenesses and challenges just KEPT popping up.
I KEPT calling them in.
And sometimes, it was overwhelming.
⠀
But more recently, I’ve seen many of my own cycles of healing…end.
⠀
Perhaps not forever—but most certainly for the time being, certain things are just the new normal now.
⠀
After ALL THAT FUCKING WORK 🥲 it…worked.
⠀
You won’t be in cycles of healing forever and ever.
⠀
There will be many moments where you feel your patterns coming into completion.
⠀
You will feel the return on energetic and emotional investment of the work you’re doing right now.
⠀
Your skills will compound over time, making things easier and easier.
⠀
Love and light—but like, FOR REAL—can overwhelm your life.
⠀
Have a beautiful weekend, my loves<3
